# Supply chain security configuration
#
# Strategy: Opcion B — native npm tools instead of ignore-scripts=true
#
# ignore-scripts=true was evaluated and discarded. It breaks three critical
# direct dependencies that require lifecycle scripts to function:
#   - @prisma/client + @prisma/engines (postinstall: generates client and downloads query engine binaries)
#   - puppeteer (postinstall: downloads Chromium binary)
#   - bcrypt (install: compiles native addon via node-pre-gyp)
#
# Mitigations in place:
#   1. min-release-age=1 — rejects packages published less than 1 day ago (typosquatting/early compromise)
#   2. npm audit signatures — verifies registry signatures on every install (run: npm audit signatures)
#   3. npm audit — vulnerability scanning (run periodically or in CI)

min-release-age=1
